I was luckily enough to go to one of her talks when she was in Oxford promoting hagseed and I recognise the wit she showed then, in these essays. So many were about incredibly important topics, such as climate change and women’s rights and were handled in a sensitive, intellectual but accessible and interesting way. The essays/obituaries concerning other authors inspired me to look into their work. I like coming away from a book with other books to read.
